By Salisu Sani-Idris Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association (MACBAN), has directed its State Chapters to cooperate fully with the security agencies in their effort to address security challenges facing the country. The National Secretary of MACBAN, Alhaji Baba Ngelzarma, made this known in a statement made available to newsmen on Tuesday in Abuja. Ngelzarma also revealed that MACBAN had resolved to bar its leaders from individually having direct dealings with any criminal group in the name of dialogue. He said that the association had confirmed Alhaji Hussaini Bosso, who until now was the Vice President I of MACBAN, as Acting President of Miyetti Allah. The national secretary explained that the emergence of Bosso as the acting President of MACBAN was necessitated by the resignation of its President, Alhaji Muhammadu Kiruwa. He also said that the association confirmed Alhaji Jauro Gari who was Vice President II to act as acting Vice President I. “The National Executive Council of MACBAN accepted the resignation of its President, Alhaji Muhammadu Kiruwa with immediate effect following the association’s emergency Executive Council meeting held in Abuja. “Kiruwa had submitted his letter of resignation, dated January 20, 2022, citing personal reasons. He had served the association as President for seven years, 10 months. “Accepting his resignation, MACBAN thanked him for steering the association through very difficult times and wished him success in his future endeavours. Ngelzarma, on behalf of MACBAN, thanked the Chairman, Board of Trustees (BOT) of the association, the Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Abubakar Sa’ad III, for his support and guidance. (NAN) (www.nannews.ng)